Flexbox makes layout easy. Apply it to the parent:

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;  /* horizontal */
  align-items: center;      /* vertical */
  gap: 16px;
}
```

The children automatically lay out in a row. Done!

Grid is for 2D layouts (rows AND columns):

```css
.grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 16px;
}
```

This creates 3 equal columns. `1fr` means '1 fraction of available space'.

CSS variables let you reuse values:

```css
:root {
  --primary-color: #6366f1;
  --spacing-md: 16px;
}

.button {
  background: var(--primary-color);
  padding: var(--spacing-md);
}
```

Change `--primary-color` once, updates everywhere!

Add smooth animations with `transition`:

```css
.button {
  background: blue;
  transition: background 0.3s ease;
}

.button:hover {
  background: darkblue;
}
```

Now hovering smoothly animates the background color!

For multi-step animations, use `@keyframes`:

```css
@keyframes bounce {
  0%   { transform: translateY(0); }
  50%  { transform: translateY(-20px); }
  100% { transform: translateY(0); }
}

.ball {
  animation: bounce 0.6s ease-in-out infinite;
}
```

Media queries let you apply different styles at different screen sizes:

```css
/* Mobile first: base styles are for mobile */
.container { padding: 16px; }

/* Then add styles for larger screens */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .container { padding: 32px; }
}
```
